Loading the Dataset

This dataset was produced from UCSD EHR records :

df <- read.csv("final_dataset.csv", header=TRUE)

Exclusion Criteria

So, now we need to exclude people based on certain factors. There are two primary exclusion criteria, the first being that patients must have been in care in the UC system 6 months prior to their surgery (ie we dont want people who just came to UC for surgery, as they will skew the results towards non-significance)

Bivariate Associations

bi.final <- data.frame(matrix(nrow = 0, ncol = 3))## create a table for bivariate results

for(i in 3:ncol(clean_data))
{
  iv <- colnames(clean_data)[i]  # gets the variable name for the column
  possibleError <- tryCatch( # we need to check for an error because the column data may not be regressable (ie only one value for the variable for all participants)
    bi.model <- glm (any_glaucoma_surgey ~ get(iv), data = clean_data, family = binomial(link="logit")), error = function(e) e
  )
  
  if(!inherits(possibleError, "error")){
    
    possibleError2 <- tryCatch(bi.results <- exp(cbind(OR = coef(bi.model), confint(bi.model))), error = function(e) e) ## similar error check
    if(!inherits(possibleError2, "error")){
      rownames(bi.results)[2] <- colnames(clean_data)[i]
      bi.final <- rbind(bi.final, bi.results)
    }
  }
  
}
# this table represents all variables found to be significant and their OR
bi.signif <- bi.final[which(bi.final$`2.5 %` > 1 | bi.final$`97.5 %`<1),]

Logisitc Regression 5-Fold Cross Validation

So, we are going to run the 5-fold cross val 100 times and return the results (mean AUC, SD). We shall utilize a bi-directional stepwise logistic regression function to run the analyses on 80% of the data set and then predict on the other fifth of the data set

runfold <- function(train, test)
{
  
  model.null = glm(any_glaucoma_surgey ~ 1, 
                 data=train,
                 family = binomial(link="logit")
                 )
  
  model.full= glm(any_glaucoma_surgey ~ Age + Gender +systolic_max + systolic_min + systolic_mean  + diastolic_max + diastolic_min + diastolic_mean +pulse_min + pulse_max + pulse_mean  +ever_hospitalized + days_hospitalized + CHF + PVD + Stroke + Dementia + Pulmonary + LiverMild + DM + DMcx  + Renal + Cancer + Mets + med_class.Analgesics_._non.opioids + med_class.Analgesics_._opioids  +  med_class.Anti.rheumatic +  med_class.Antianxiety_agents  + med_class.Antiasthmatic + med_class.Anticoagulants + med_class.Anticonvulsant + med_class.Antidepressants + med_class.Antidiabetic + med_class.Antiemetics + med_class.Antihyperlipidemic + med_class.Antihypertensive + med_class.Beta_blockers + med_class.Calcium_blockers + med_class.Corticosteroids + med_class.Cough.Cold + med_class.Decongestants + med_class.Dermatological + med_class.Diuretics + med_class.Laxatives + med_class.Macrolide_antibiotics + med_class.Misc._antiinfectives + med_class.Ophthalmic+med_class.Ulcer_drugs, 
                 data=train,
                 family = binomial(link="logit")
                 )
  
  step.results <- step(model.null,
     scope = list(upper=model.full),
             direction="both",
             test="Chisq",
             data=train, trace = 0)
  
  final.model <- eval(step.results$call)
  lr.pr <- predict(final.model, test, type="response") # this sequence used to plot the ROC Curve
  lr.pred <- ROCR::prediction(lr.pr,test$any_glaucoma_surgey)
  
  auc_curve <- ROCR::performance(lr.pred,"tpr","fpr")
  
  auc <- ROCR::performance(lr.pred,"auc")@y.values[[1]]
  
  return(list(auc,auc_curve))
}

## this function will randomize the data into five even groups and run
## the cross validations, returning an average AUC and the AUC curves 
## of each of the cross validations
fivefold <- function(data){
  
#create a vector with the appropriate number of 1,2,3,4,5
values <- rep(1:5, length.out=nrow(data))
#randomly sort this vector
random <- sample(values)
#add this vector to the data, essentially assigning each row a random group
data$cv_group <- random


## next we want to assign the five test and training pairings
train.one <- data[which(data$cv_group!= 1),]
test.one <- data[which(data$cv_group== 1),]
train.two <- data[which(data$cv_group!= 2),]
test.two <- data[which(data$cv_group== 2),]
train.three <- data[which(data$cv_group!= 3),]
test.three <- data[which(data$cv_group== 3),]
train.four <- data[which(data$cv_group!= 4),]
test.four <- data[which(data$cv_group== 4),]
train.five <- data[which(data$cv_group!= 5),]
test.five <- data[which(data$cv_group== 5),]

res1 <- runfold(train.one, test.one)
res2 <- runfold(train.two, test.two)
res3 <- runfold(train.three, test.three)
res4 <- runfold(train.four, test.four)
res5 <- runfold(train.five, test.five)


aucs <- c(res1[1][[1]],res2[1][[1]],res3[1][[1]],res4[1][[1]],res5[1][[1]])
auc_curves <- list(res1[2][[1]],res2[2][[1]],res3[2][[1]],res4[2][[1]],res5[2][[1]])

#plot(res1[2][[1]])
#plot(res2[2][[1]], add = TRUE)
return(list(aucs, auc_curves))
  
}

auc_curves <- list()
mean_aucs <- c()

for(i in 1:100){
  kfold_result <- fivefold(clean_data)
  
  mean_aucs <- c(mean_aucs, mean(kfold_result[[1]])) 
  
  for(j in 1:5)
  {
    auc_curves <- append(auc_curves, kfold_result[[2]][[j]])
  }
  
}

count <- 0
evaluation_string <- ""
for (i in 1:length(auc_curves)) {
  if(count == 0)
  {
    new_string <- paste("plot(auc_curves[[",i,"]],main='ROC Curve for Logistic Regression',col=2,lwd=2)", sep ="")
    evaluation_string <- new_string
    count <- 1
  } else {
    new_string <- paste("plot(auc_curves[[",i,"]], add = TRUE, col = 2)", sep ="")
    evaluation_string <- paste(evaluation_string, new_string, sep = "\n")
  }
}

runfold_rf <- function(train, test)
{
  
  model.rf = randomForest(any_glaucoma_surgey ~ Age + Gender +systolic_max + systolic_min + systolic_mean  + diastolic_max + diastolic_min + diastolic_mean +pulse_min + pulse_max + pulse_mean  +ever_hospitalized + days_hospitalized + CHF + PVD + Stroke + Dementia + Pulmonary + LiverMild + DM + DMcx  + Renal + Cancer + Mets + med_class.Analgesics_._non.opioids + med_class.Analgesics_._opioids  +  med_class.Anti.rheumatic +  med_class.Antianxiety_agents  + med_class.Antiasthmatic + med_class.Anticoagulants + med_class.Anticonvulsant + med_class.Antidepressants + med_class.Antidiabetic + med_class.Antiemetics + med_class.Antihyperlipidemic + med_class.Antihypertensive + med_class.Beta_blockers + med_class.Calcium_blockers + med_class.Corticosteroids + med_class.Cough.Cold + med_class.Decongestants + med_class.Dermatological + med_class.Diuretics + med_class.Laxatives + med_class.Macrolide_antibiotics + med_class.Misc._antiinfectives + med_class.Ophthalmic + med_class.Ulcer_drugs, 
                 data=train, importance = TRUE, mtry = 6
                 )
  
  pr <- predict(model.rf, test, type="prob")[,2] # this sequence used to plot the ROC Curve
  pred <- ROCR::prediction(pr,test$any_glaucoma_surgey)
  
  auc_curve <- ROCR::performance(pred,"tpr","fpr")
  
  auc <- ROCR::performance(pred,"auc")@y.values[[1]]
  
  return(list(auc,auc_curve))
}

## this function will randomize the data into five even groups and run
## the cross validations, returning an average AUC and the AUC curves 
## of each of the cross validations
fivefold_rf <- function(data){
  
#create a vector with the appropriate number of 1,2,3,4,5
values <- rep(1:5, length.out=nrow(data))
#randomly sort this vector
random <- sample(values)
#add this vector to the data, essentially assigning each row a random group
data$cv_group <- random


## next we want to assign the five test and training pairings
train.one <- data[which(data$cv_group!= 1),]
test.one <- data[which(data$cv_group== 1),]
train.two <- data[which(data$cv_group!= 2),]
test.two <- data[which(data$cv_group== 2),]
train.three <- data[which(data$cv_group!= 3),]
test.three <- data[which(data$cv_group== 3),]
train.four <- data[which(data$cv_group!= 4),]
test.four <- data[which(data$cv_group== 4),]
train.five <- data[which(data$cv_group!= 5),]
test.five <- data[which(data$cv_group== 5),]

res1 <- runfold_rf(train.one, test.one)
res2 <- runfold_rf(train.two, test.two)
res3 <- runfold_rf(train.three, test.three)
res4 <- runfold_rf(train.four, test.four)
res5 <- runfold_rf(train.five, test.five)


aucs <- c(res1[1][[1]],res2[1][[1]],res3[1][[1]],res4[1][[1]],res5[1][[1]])
auc_curves <- list(res1[2][[1]],res2[2][[1]],res3[2][[1]],res4[2][[1]],res5[2][[1]])

#plot(res1[2][[1]])
#plot(res2[2][[1]], add = TRUE)
return(list(aucs, auc_curves))
  
}

  model.ann <- neuralnet(any_glaucoma_surgey ~ Age + Gender +systolic_max + systolic_min + systolic_mean  + diastolic_max + diastolic_min + diastolic_mean +pulse_min + pulse_max + pulse_mean  +ever_hospitalized + days_hospitalized + CHF + PVD + Stroke + Dementia + Pulmonary + LiverMild + DM + DMcx  + Renal + Cancer + Mets + med_class.Analgesics_._non.opioids + med_class.Analgesics_._opioids  +  med_class.Anti.rheumatic +  med_class.Antianxiety_agents  + med_class.Antiasthmatic + med_class.Anticoagulants + med_class.Anticonvulsant + med_class.Antidepressants + med_class.Antidiabetic + med_class.Antiemetics + med_class.Antihyperlipidemic + med_class.Antihypertensive + med_class.Beta_blockers + med_class.Calcium_blockers + med_class.Corticosteroids + med_class.Cough.Cold + med_class.Decongestants + med_class.Dermatological + med_class.Diuretics + med_class.Laxatives + med_class.Macrolide_antibiotics + med_class.Misc._antiinfectives + med_class.Ophthalmic + med_class.Ulcer_drugs, 
                 data=train, hidden = c(32,16), threshold = 0.01
                 )

fivefold_ann <- function(data){
  
#create a vector with the appropriate number of 1,2,3,4,5
values <- rep(1:5, length.out=nrow(data))
#randomly sort this vector
